definition.value: A reduction of joint mobility resulting from changes involving the articular surfaces.

label.value: Alternating radiolucent and radiodense metaphyseal lines

definition.value: Nuclear lobes of neutrophils in the bone marrow are thickened and condensed, and individual lobes are connected by unusually long chromatin filaments.
A larger than normal amount or percentage of hematopoietic cells relative to marrow fat.
A benign epithelial neoplasm characterized by a papillary growth pattern and a proliferation of neoplastic squamous cells without morphologic evidence of malignancy [NCI thesaurus].
A benign exophytic neoplasm that arises from the oropharynx. It is characterized by the presence of a connective tissue core covered by stratified squamous epithelium [NCI thesaurus].

label.value: Internal notch of the femoral head
Abnormal insulin like growth factor binding protein acid labile subunit level

definition.value: Presence of a protracted or persistent infection by a pathogen potentially related to an underlying abnormality of the immune system that is not able to clear the infection.
A decreased blood concentration of growth hormone binding protein.

label.value: Obstruction of the superior vena cava

definition.value: Blockage of blood flow through the superior vena cava (SVC). Because the venous drainage from the upper extremities, upper thorax and head is obstructed, SVC obstruction presents with symptoms related to engorgement of these areas. Both the degree of SVC compromise and the extent of collateral veins determine the varied clinical presentation, which can be as mild as slight facial and upper extremity edema or as dire as intracranial swelling, seizures, hemodynamic instability and tracheal obstruction.
Bullae (defined as fluid-filled blisters more than 5 mm in diameter with thin walls) of the skin with an acral distribution (affecting peripheral regions such as hands and feet).
An abnormal immunoglobulin light chain in the circulation and typically produced by a clonal population of B-cell derived plasma cells.
An abnormal immunoglobulin (heavy and light chain) in the circulation and typically produced by a clonal population of B-cell derived plasma cells.
An elevation in bone density in one or more tarsal bones of the foot. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

label.value: Elevated vascular endothelial growth factor level

definition.value: Increased blood concentration of vascular endothelial growth factor (VEGF).

label.value: Coarctation in the transverse aortic arch

definition.value: Narrowing or constriction of the aorta localized to the region of the transverse aortic arch.

label.value: Long segment coarctation of the aorta
Abnormal branching pattern of left aortic arch

definition.value: A deviance from the norm of the origin or course of the right brachiocephalic artery, the left common carotid artery, the left subclavian artery or the proximal vertebral arteries, whereby the aortic arch descends on the left as normal (as opposed to right aortic arch).
A localized circumferential (i.e., bulges on all sides) dilatation or ballooning of a cerebral artery.
A clearly-defined and roughly linear cleavage in the skin that usually extends to the dermis.

label.value: Impairment of activities of daily living

definition.value: Difficulty in performing one or more activities normally performed every day, such as eating, bathing, dressing, grooming, work, homemaking, and leisure.
This term applies to an individual who requires help transferring to the toilet, cleaning self or who uses bedpan or commode.
